Roman Agora

Time spent there: 25 min

Entrance: here

During the 1st century BC, the commercial center of the city was transferred from the Ancient Agora to the Roman Agora. When Romans came, they converted the Ancient Agora into a place of cult for the Emperor and moved the business outside.

Tower of the Winds : cadran solaire and hydraulic clock

Mosque

The ruins are very visible from the outside if you don't want to pay the combined ticket.
